        {
          "field_id": "the_presence_of_necrosis_is_correlated_with_the_finding_of_mammographic_calcifications_ie_most_areas",
          "label": "The presence of necrosis is correlated with the finding of mammographic calcifications (i.e., most areas of necrosis will calcify). Ductal carcinoma in situ that presents as mammographic calcifications often recurs as calcifications. Necrosis can be classified as follows",
          "required": true,
